python bot.py --strategy bollinger_bands --symbol BTCUSD --timeframe 5s --period 20 --std 0.5 --bb-stop-loss 0.3 --bb-take-profit 0.6 --bb-volume-multiplier 1.0 --poll-interval 10

Key differences across timeframes:

Param	5m	15m	1h
--std	2.0	2.0	2.0
--bb-stop-loss	0.6	0.8	1.0
--bb-take-profit	1.2	1.5	2.0
--poll-interval	60s	120s	300s
Wider SL/TP on higher timeframes to account for larger candle ranges. Start with 15m for the best balance of signal frequency and reliability.


--- production settings

python bot.py \
  --symbol BTCUSD \
  --timeframe 15m \
  --poll 60 \
  --bb-period 20 \
  --bb-std 2.0 \
  --bb-stop-loss 0.5 \
  --bb-take-profit 1.0 \
  --bb-trail-activation 0.5 \
  --bb-trail-pct 0.3 \
  --bb-tp-extension 0.3 \
  --bb-volume-period 20 \
  --bb-volume-multiplier 1.0

What each parameter means at 15m
Parameter	Value	Reasoning
--bb-period	20	Standard BB period, looks back 5 hours on 15m
--bb-std	2.0	Classic 2 std deviation bands, filters noise well
--bb-stop-loss	0.5	0.5% SL - tight enough to limit loss, wide enough for 15m candle variance
--bb-take-profit	1.0	2:1 reward/risk ratio
--bb-trail-activation	0.5	Trail kicks in after 0.5% profit
--bb-trail-pct	0.3	Trails 0.3% behind best price
--bb-tp-extension	0.3	Extends TP by 0.3% if momentum continues
--poll	60	Check every 60s - no need to poll faster than candle close


Once stable - adding ETHUSD and XAUTUSD
Run each symbol in a separate terminal / process:

# Terminal 1 - BTCUSD
python bot.py --symbol BTCUSD --timeframe 15m --poll 60 --bb-std 2.0 --bb-stop-loss 0.5 --bb-take-profit 1.0

# Terminal 2 - ETHUSD (after BTCUSD is stable)
python bot.py --symbol ETHUSD --timeframe 15m --poll 60 --bb-std 2.0 --bb-stop-loss 0.5 --bb-take-profit 1.0

# Terminal 3 - XAUTUSD (after ETHUSD is stable)
python bot.py --symbol XAUTUSD --timeframe 15m --poll 60 --bb-std 2.0 --bb-stop-loss 0.5 --bb-take-profit 1.0




